(143, 1, '2010-03-03 00:04:22', '2010-03-03 00:04:22', '<p><img class=" alignleft size-full wp-image-142" src="http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/in-the-realm-of-hungry-g-c.jpg" border="0" alt="In the Realm of Hungry Ghosts Cover" title="In the Realm of Hungry Ghosts by Gabor Mate, MD" align="left" width="188" height="288" /> <br /><br /><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Realm-Hungry-Ghosts-Encounters-Addiction/dp/155643880X/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&s=books&qid=1267574807&sr=1-1" target="_blank" title="Purchase Through Amazon">Purchase through Amazon</a></p> <p> </p> <p style="text-align: left;" />  <!--more-->  <br />In the Realm of Hungry Ghosts Cover“Gabor Mate’s connections – between the intensely personal and the global and spiritual and the medical, the psychological and the political – are bold, wise and deeply moral. He is a healer to be cherished and this exciting book arrives at just the right time.”<br /><br /><em>Naomi Klein, author of No Logo and The Shock Doctrine.</em></p>', 'In the Realm of Hungry Ghosts: Encounters with Addiction by Gabor Mate', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'in-the-realm-of-hungry-ghosts-encounters-with-addiction-by-gabor-mate', '', '', '2010-03-03 00:04:22', '2010-03-03 00:04:22', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2010/03/03/in-the-realm-of-hungry-ghosts-encounters-with-addiction-by-gabor-mate/', 15, 'post', '', 0),
(144, 1, '2010-03-03 00:27:56', '2010-03-03 00:27:56', '<p>Unfortunately, due to his current time constraints, he is unable to see private clients. However, he has 5,000 people training in Somatic Experiencing globally, and the best way is to check out the <a href="http://www.traumahealing.com/somatic-experiencing/practitioner-directory.html" target="_blank" title="Find a Practitioner">Practitioners Registry</a> There are still chances to see him by checking out his events page.</p>', 'Does Peter see private clients?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'does-peter-see-private-clients', '', '', '2010-03-03 00:27:56', '2010-03-03 00:27:56', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2010/03/03/does-peter-see-private-clients/', 2, 'post', '', 0),
(145, 1, '2010-03-03 00:31:40', '2010-03-03 00:31:40', '<p>Everyone has questions about trauma, what it is, and how to get help. Unfortunately, Peter can''t guide everyone. It is unethical for him to give case consultations or advice to anyone that he is not directly related to. If you are looking for help with a trauma issue, we recommend that you find a Somatic Experiencing Practitioner (SEP) in your area, please see the <a href="http://www.traumahealing.com/somatic-experiencing/practitioner-directory.html" target="_blank" title="Find a Practitioner">Practitioners Registry</a> at the traumahealing website for the Foundation for Human Enrichment, a non-profit organization started by Peter, to oversee the training of therapists in his techniques. <br /><br /></p>', 'I have a question about trauma, can you help?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'i-have-a-question-about-trauma-can-you-help', '', '', '2010-03-03 00:31:40', '2010-03-03 00:31:40', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2010/03/03/i-have-a-question-about-trauma-can-you-help/', 1, 'post', '', 0),
(146, 1, '2010-03-03 01:28:46', '2010-03-03 01:28:46', 'In distinction to cognitive and emotional based therapies (“top-down” approaches which focus on insight and emotions first and only secondarily focus on somatic responses to trauma), SE® is a “bottom-up” approach.\n\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">It focuses on the brain stem and its survival-based functions which are not under conscious or emotional control. Access to these instinctual action and arousal systems is through the vehicle of physical bodily sensations. Cognitions and emotions are included in SE® practice but they are secondary or derivative from physical sensations through bottom-up processing.</span>', 'Somatic Experiencing Compared', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'somatic-experiencing-compared', '', '', '2010-03-03 01:28:46', '2010-03-03 01:28:46', '', 94, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2010/03/03/somatic-experiencing-compared/', 1, 'page', '', 0);
