(175, 1, '2010-08-09 23:15:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p><em>For members of the Somatic Experiencing®Training Program Only:</em></p> <p>Peter is coming to the San Francisco area to recieve a Lifetime Achievment award from the <a href="http://usabp.org/displayconvention.cfm?conventionnbr=7093" title="USABP Conference Info" target="_blank">United States Association for Body Pschotherapy</a>.</p> <p> </p> <p style="float: right; background-color: #eeeeee; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding: 4px; border: 1px solid #dddddd;"><img class=" size-full wp-image-171" alt="Peter Pic" height="150" width="200" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/esalen21.jpg" width="2592" height="1944" /></p> <p>As part of his lifetime achievement award with <a href="http://usabp.org/" title="USABP Homepage" target="_blank">USABP</a>, Dr. Levine will be offering two events in the Tiburon/Northern California area. The first will be a one-day Group Case Consultation that is open to ALL levels of SE<span style="font-weight: bold;">®&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: normal;">training on October 28th, 2010. The second will be a 3 day workshop for SE Practitioners and Students who have completed Advanced Level I on dealing with Near Death and Anesthesia states, October 29th, through 31st, 2010. </span></span></p> <p> </p> <p>This is the first part of a two part class, that Dr. Levine has taught throughout Europe, and is finally bringing to the US.&nbsp;</p>  <!--more-->  <h5 style="font-size: 1.4em;">Group Case Consultation - October 28th, 2010. Open to all levels.</h5> <p>Location:Tiburon, TBA</p> <p>Costs/enrollment:&nbsp;Please contact coordinator&nbsp;<a style="outline-width: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-color: initial; font-size: 18px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px initial initial;" href="mailto:andrea@easethebody.com" title="Email Andrea Smith" target="_blank">Andrea Smith</a> for more information.</p> <p> </p> <h5 style="font-size: 1.4em;">Through the Eye of the Needle: Working with Near Death and Anesthesia States: For Post-Advanced Somatic Experiencing® Practitioners Only:</h5> <p><img class=" alignright size-full wp-image-172" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/vortex-8001.jpg" width="200" height="150" alt="Vortex" style="float: right;" width="800" height="600" /></p> <p>In the USA over 29 million patients utilize powerful dissociative and amnesic agents…“general anesthesia”. Some individuals experience states of death from which they are revived. In fact,some of the deepest and seemingly most intractable trauma symptoms occur with clients who become “stuck” in these altered states of consciousness. Yet these same near death experiences(NDE’s) hold the extraordinary potential for deep positive and enduring personal spiritual transformation. All traumas involve an encounter with threat, and hence, a touch with death. This workshop, broken up over two classes, is the next step to enlarge your range of competency in order to guide your client through this perilous landscape. Participants will be taught the theoretical framework for understanding altered states and near death encounters and how to:</p> <ul> <li>access and liberate problematic fixations</li> <li>develop and refine perceptual skills and practical tools</li> <li>resolve difficult somatic symptoms</li> <li>facilitate authentic spiritual experiences</li> <li>address these delicate states utilizing table touch work (experiential).</li> </ul> <p><img class=" alignright size-full wp-image-173" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/WaterVortex1.jpg" width="300" height="200" alt="Water Vortex" style="float: right;" width="1024" height="683" /></p> <p> </p> <blockquote>God of the traumatized, grant Your empathetic, all understanding comfort of Your beloved and innocentchildren all over the world who have suffered the unspeakable terror of anesthesia awareness. Hold with gentle firmness those who cannot express what happened to them or how traumatic their experience was and is. ~ <em><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Prayer for Anesthesia Awareness Network</span></em></blockquote> <p>This is the first of two parts for working with Near Death States. Eye of the Needle Part II is planned for April 1st through the 4th. Don''t missed this exciting opportunity.&nbsp;</p> <p>Click <a target="_blank" title="Sign up form" href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/eontiburonsignup1.pdf">here</a> the Sign up form. For more information on the class, please contact coordinator&nbsp;<a href="mailto:andrea@easethebody.com" title="Email Andrea SMith" target="_blank" style="outline-width: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-color: initial; font-size: 18px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px initial initial;">Andrea Smith</a>.</p>', 'Two Workshops for SEP''s being held in Northern California', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'two-workshops-for-seps-happening-in-northern-california', '', '', '2010-08-09 23:15:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/?p=175', 18, 'post', '', 0),
