(207, 1, '2013-01-29 20:42:29', '2013-01-29 20:42:29', '<p align="center" style="line-height: 150%; text-align: left;">Dr. Levine will be in London, England from May 25th to the 26th for the Breath of Life Conference for 2013. This Conference is for Cranial Sacral Therapists, and we are proud to be in partnership with them.</p> <p align="center" style="line-height: 150%; text-align: left;">Dr. Levine will be presenting a keynote, entitled:&nbsp;<a href="#keynote"><b style="line-height: 150%;">Spirituality and Trauma: From Trauma to Awakening and Flow</b></a> as well as a 2 day Post Conference Workshop, entitled: <a href="#workshop"><strong><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Emotional Self-Regulation: the Body and Change</span></strong></a><a href="#workshop"><strong>Working with Difficult Feelings</strong></a>(Click each link for a short description).&nbsp;</p> <p>The Breath of Life enrollment is available directly through their website. For More information and to enroll, please visit the&nbsp;<a href="http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/" title="Breath of Life London''s website." target="_blank">Breath of Life conference website</a></p> <p>Click Read More:</p> <p> <!--more--> </p> <h6 align="center" style="line-height: 1.2em; font-size: 1.2em;"><a name="keynote">Spirituality and Trauma;&nbsp;From Trauma to Awakening and Flow</a></h6> <p>In the treatment of the effects of trauma, its inherent relationship with spirituality provides a vital link in the therapeutic process.&nbsp; The understanding of a person''s, felt, spiritual connection is central to the therapeutic process.&nbsp; If we are unable to access a person''s spirituality, we may find ourselves trapped, as therapists, in areas that are fraught with pitfalls and "tight corners".&nbsp; The intimate association between trauma and spirituality suggests therapeutic avenues that support the authentic transformation of traumatic experiences.</p> <p style="line-height: 150%;"><a href=".../images/stories/articles/bol-2013_UK/bol_large.jpg" title="Link to larger image" target="_blank"><img class=" size-full wp-image-205" src="http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bol_small.jpg" width="196" height="277" alt="breath of life small" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding: 4px; border: 2px solid #246da5;" width="196" height="277" /></a></p> <p style="line-height: 150%;">&nbsp;</p> <p style="line-height: 150%;">Through the use of didactic material- including brain research, experiential practice incorporating the bodily "felt-sense", and video material, we will introduce Somatic Experiencing® as a way to re-connect with the deep self. &nbsp; The focus will be on developing practical tools to gracefully enhance the relationship between trauma and spirituality within the therapeutic experience. &nbsp;</p> <p style="line-height: 150%;">You can see the event listing from our <a href="https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/event-calendar.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=10" title="Our event listing" target="_blank">website</a>, or head directly to <a href="http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/" title="Breath of Life Homepage" target="_blank">BOL''s website</a>.&nbsp;</p> <p><br /> <br /><a name="workshop"></a></p> <h6 align="center" style="line-height: 1.2em; font-size: 1.2em;"><a name="workshop">Emotional Self-Regulation: the Body and ChangeWorking with Difficult Feelings</a></h6> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>In doing therapeutic work, therapists are often confused about the role of emotions. Sometimes therapists and body-workers have the idea that they are supposed to avoid emotions, and others may have been trained to “go after them—to get them out.”</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>While it is true that intense emotional eruptions can interfere with one’s life, there is a deeper truth: that helping clients access their natural emotions, and learn from them, is an important part of good depth therapy and an enhancement to life.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Emotional self-regulation, as we shall explore together, is essential to lasting integration and wholeness. In this regard we will explore how certain emotions (such as disgust and anger) are “gatekeepers” and are essential to opening to other feelings which, together, promotes a fuller, wiser, vital and creative life.</p> <p>See the <a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bol_conf_flyer1.pdf" title="Breath of Life Flyer" target="_blank">Flyer here</a>. Or go to our <a href="https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/event-calendar.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=11" title="SE.com''s event listing" target="_blank">Event listing for location info</a>, or head directly to <a href="http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/?page_id=491" title="Breath of Life workshop page" target="_blank">BOL''s website</a> to enroll</p>', 'Breath of Life Conference - This May in London, UK', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'breath-of-life-conference-this-may-in-london-uk', '', '', '2013-01-29 20:42:29', '2013-01-29 20:42:29', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/01/29/breath-of-life-conference-this-may-in-london-uk/', 8, 'post', '', 0),
(208, 1, '2013-01-29 21:54:09', '2013-01-29 21:54:09', '<p align="center"><img src="https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/Gallery/attachment_hero.jpg" alt="UCLA Conference - Attachment and Neuroplasticity" style="border: 2px solid #246da5; display: block; padding: 4px;" /></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>We are happy to announce that March 8th through the 10th, Dr. Levine has been invited to speak at UCLA''s Extension and Lifespan Learning Institute''s conference; entitled - How People Change: Relationships and Neuroplasticity in Psychotherapy.</p> <p>This presentation is open to the public. For more information, <a href="https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/default.aspx" title="UCLA Extension website" target="_blank">please visit here:</a></p> <p><a href="https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/Gallery/2013%20Attachment%20Conference%20Brochure.pdf" title="Conference Brochure" target="_blank">PDF brochure is here:</a>&nbsp;</p> <p><a href="http://maps.ucla.edu/campus/?locid=83759" title="UCLA interactive map" target="_blank">Located in the Ackerman Grand Ballroom</a>. (Link will take you to a lovely interactive map of UCLA''s campus). You''re welcome.</p>', 'UCLA Presents - How People Change: Relationships and Neuroplasticity in Psychotherapy', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ucla-presents-how-people-change-relationships-and-neuroplasticity-in-psychotherapy', '', '', '2013-01-29 21:54:09', '2013-01-29 21:54:09', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/01/29/ucla-presents-how-people-change-relationships-and-neuroplasticity-in-psychotherapy/', 7, 'post', '', 0),
(209, 1, '2013-01-30 00:21:29', '2013-12-17 00:46:28', '', 'se_masterclass-bw_pv_syndromes_apr_2013', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'se_masterclass-bw_pv_syndromes_apr_2013', '', '', '2013-01-30 00:21:29', '2013-12-17 00:46:28', '', 211, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/se_masterclass-bw_pv_syndromes_apr_20131.pdf', 0, 'attachment', 'application/pdf', 0),
(211, 1, '2013-01-30 00:21:29', '2013-01-30 00:21:29', '<p align="center"><a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/se_masterclass-bw_pv_syndromes_apr_20131.pdf" title="See the Flyer (PDF)" target="_blank"><img class=" size-full wp-image-210" src="http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Polyvagal-syndromes2.jpg" alt="Polyvagal-syndromes2" style="border: 2px solid #246da5; display: block; padding: 4px;" width="750" height="300" width="750" height="300" /></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>The Somatic Experiencing® Trauma Institute is proud to present another in a series of post advanced courses, taught by Dr. Peter A Levine. These classes are designed to enhance and extend your skillsets that you have been developing in the 3 year SE® Training.&nbsp;<br /><br />Location: <a href="http://book.bestwestern.com/bestwestern/US/CA/Corte-Madera-hotels/BEST-WESTERN-PLUS-Corte-Madera-Inn/Hotel-Overview.do?propertyCode=05259" title="Corte Madera Inn''s homepage." target="_blank">Corte Madera Best Western Inn</a> -&nbsp;56 Madera Blvd &nbsp;Corte Madera, CA 94925</p> <p>Dates: April 18th-22nd, 2013</p> <p>Price: $1495 ($200 if you sign up before March 18th!)</p> <p>How to Enroll: Call 303-652-4035 or email <a href="mailto:info@traumahealing.com">info@traumahealing.com</a>&nbsp;(subject: Master Class Enrollement)</p> <p>Click "Read More" to the right to see the class description</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>  <!--more-->  <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <div style="background-color: #c9c9c9; color: #2c1dgf; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, San-serif;"> <p style="text-align: center;">Advanced Bodywork, Polyvagal Theory, and Complex Syndromes</p> <p style="text-align: center;">A Master Class With SE Founder</p> <p style="text-align: center;">Peter A Levine, PhD</p> <p>The Polyvagal Theory of Stephen Porges, PhD, is a critically important neuro-scientific map for informing precise Somatic Experiencing® interventions. This is particularly true when working directly with SE® bodywork. Porges’ theory guides us in precisely assessing where a client is stuck so that we can support their movement out of shutdown and numbness, to contained arousal, and then to establish core equilibrium, social engagement and enduring feelings of presence, vitality and goodness. Preparing you, the therapist, to competently achieve these lofty (though attainable) goals is the aim of this Master Class.</p> <p>In addition, we will delve into how SE® based bodywork can treat complex syndromes caused by core autonomic dysregulation. These syndromes include migraines, asthma, fibromyalgia, Irritable Bowel Syndrome, Chronic Fatigue Syndrome, Regional Complex Pain Syndrome, as well as, low heart rate or blood pressure, certain cardiac arrhythmias, light headedness, fainting (syncope), and a variety of auto-immune diseases. You will learn why individuals frequently present with these problematic and mutating symptoms, and how they are also associated with various anxiety disorders and depressive conditions. We will expand upon our basic SE® techniques and discover how to treat these syndromes as a cohesive whole. The class will be a mixture of didactic lecture, live demonstrations and hands-on experiential practice.</p> <p>While this training is primarily for individuals who have completed their advanced level training by the time of the master class, it will also be opened to a few skilled body workers who have completed their intermediate level training. While the focus of this special class is on advanced applications of SE Bodywork, it is also open to psycho therapists with some bodywork experience who are wishing to advance their skills.</p> <p><em>Suggested Preparation</em></p> <p>It is important to have (re) read chapters 5&amp;6 in: <a href="http://www.amazon.com/In-Unspoken-Voice-Releases-Restores/dp/1556439431/ref=pd_bxgy_b_img_y" title="Amazon Page for In an Unsoken Voice" target="_blank">In an Unspoken Voice; How the Body Releases Trauma and Restores Goodness</a>. Additionally, it would be useful to review some of Dr. Porges book: <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Polyvagal-Theory-Neurophysiological-Communication-Self-regulation/dp/0393707008" title="Amazon page for Polyvagal Theory" target="_blank">The Polyvagal Theory: Neurophysiological Foundations of Emotions, Attachment, Communication, and Self-regulation</a> (Norton Series on Interpersonal Neurobiology)</p> </div>', 'UPDATED---Advanced Bodywork, Polyvagal Theory, and Complex Syndromes - Master Class in Corte Madera, Ca', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'advanced-bodywork-polyvagal-theory-and-complex-syndromes-master-class-in-corte-madera-ca', '', '', '2013-01-30 00:21:29', '2013-01-30 00:21:29', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/01/30/advanced-bodywork-polyvagal-theory-and-complex-syndromes-master-class-in-corte-madera-ca/', 5, 'post', '', 0),
(212, 1, '2013-01-30 01:16:38', '2013-01-30 01:16:38', '<p>One of Peter''s classic videos - Jody, My Ears, My Tears and My Fears, is one of the seminal training videos in the Somatic Experiencing®.&nbsp;</p> <h3>Jody-</h3> <p>&nbsp;</p> <br /> <iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/58570494" width="500" height="375" frameborder="0" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe>', 'Jody - My Ears, My Tears, My Fears', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jody-my-ears-my-tears-my-fears', '', '', '2013-01-30 01:16:38', '2013-01-30 01:16:38', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/01/30/jody-my-ears-my-tears-my-fears/', 4, 'post', '', 0),
(213, 1, '2013-02-04 23:35:39', '2013-02-04 23:35:39', '<p><a href="http://www.womenssymposium.org/index.php" title="Go to Register Now" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.womenssymposium.org/images/2013-save-the-date.jpg" alt="Womens Symposium Save the Date" width="300" height="170" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" /></a></p> <p>Dr. Levine will be participating as a speaker at the 2013 Women’s Symposium. The Women’s Symposium is a one-day event featuring women leaders in the field of addiction, behavioral health, and women’s issues. Our 2013 Women’s Symposium message is a “Journey to Wholeness.”<span style="line-height: 1.3em;">&nbsp;This year’s topics are practical, solution-focused and designed to enrich the skills of professionals within the field of addiction treatment and those who treat addicted women.</span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Check out their site for <a href="http://www.womenssymposium.org/index.php" title="Women''s Symposium Homepage" target="_blank">more info.</a></p>', 'Speaking at the Betty Ford Center''s Women''s Symposium  on March 21st at UCLA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'speaking-at-the-betty-ford-centers-womens-symposium-on-march-21st-at-ucla', '', '', '2013-02-04 23:35:39', '2013-02-04 23:35:39', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/02/04/speaking-at-the-betty-ford-centers-womens-symposium-on-march-21st-at-ucla/', 6, 'post', '', 0);
