(214, 1, '2013-02-08 23:23:33', '2013-02-08 23:23:33', '<div style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/54418002" width="400" height="300" frameborder="0" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></div> <p>Next Friday, Dr. Levine will participate on a live panel, as part of a tele-symposim to bring awareness to the effects of human trafficking, which is a $32-billion industry worldwide. Be part of an event to raise awareness. <a href="http://magnificentminded.com/mission/mission-to-mind-health/" title="Mission to mind home page" target="_blank">Listen live or listen the recordings</a>. The press release is after the break.&nbsp;</p> <p><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">&nbsp;</span></b></p> <p><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;"></span></b></p>  <!--more-->  <p><b>Do You Know What It Takes to Make a Lifestyle Lift?</b></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>If you would like to find out...</span></p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>This free 4-part tele and web summit has been created to help people become the master of their own magnificence by enriching the mind and enhancing practices <i>and I am sharing my expertise related to –</i></span></p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>Mission to Mind Health Mastery is a free 4-part, 26 hour tele and video symposium with the goal for you to discover <b>Maximum&nbsp; - Peace Potential Performance and Prosperity</b></span></p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>Why is this important?</span></p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>Well, our experiences can shape and structure our brains and this, in turn plays a powerful role in moulding our stories.&nbsp; We want you to have the power to create your story with rich possibilities.</span></p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>Carol Soares has gathered 45 of the best brain/mind health, personal growth and transformation experts in the world for this event which continues on Friday, February 15 @ 11 am (EST). &nbsp;The focus is performance – how you interact with and “show up” in the world. Visit </span><span><a href="http://missiontomindmastery.com"></a><a href="http://missiontomindmastery.com">http://missiontomindmastery.com</a></span><span> to listen to the amazing interviews. It truly is a mind marathon focusing on many aspects of wellness! The day will include a series of 8 incredible 25-minute interviews that will help you to take away nuggets provided in small portions for applying to your daily life.&nbsp; Our collaborative mission is for the world to be equipped to tap into the power of their magnificence. That includes you!</span></p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>The mission aims to have you take away a minimum of 50 ways to fortify your mind for maximum possibilities (that you can start using immediately). This information will not only help you to optimize your mind, but because Carol is specifically dedicating the event to women/mompreneurs, if you are a woman, you’re going to take this to enrich your life, family and social life, and your business.&nbsp; </span></p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>By connecting through this event you will also help raise awareness and support for My Refuge House for girls who are survivors of sex trafficking experiences.&nbsp; The numbers of women and children affected continues to be astounding. </span></p> <p style="margin-left: 0.25in;"><span>Human trafficking is a criminal business that profits from enslaving people for sexual servitude and forced labor.</span><span> It is the fastest growing and second largest criminal industry in the world today. Human trafficking is a $32-billion industry worldwide.</span></p> <p><span>Listen live or listen the recordings. It’s up to you. We just hope that you make your personal growth a priority and listen. Register here: </span><a href="http://missiontomindmastery.com"><span></span></a><a href="http://missiontomindmastery.com">http://missiontomindmastery.com</a><span></span></p> <p><span>(and please share with others so that the messages can reach as many as possible)</span></p>', 'Bringing Awareness to Human Trafficking - February 15th, 2013', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bringing-awareness-to-human-trafficking-february-15th-2013', '', '', '2013-02-08 23:23:33', '2013-02-08 23:23:33', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/02/08/bringing-awareness-to-human-trafficking-february-15th-2013/', 3, 'post', '', 0),
(215, 1, '2013-02-12 23:38:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'It is the sincere honor of SomaticExperiencing.com to announce the release of Freedom From Pain. This program (both a standalone 2-disc Audio album and Book/CD) to not just show the links between Chronic Pain and trauma, but to provide sufferers with a "toolbox" of techniques, exercises and resources to create a custom treatment system for tackling this complex and widespread issue. Written by Dr. Levine, and his long time collaborator, colleague, SE® faculty member, and pain expert, Dr. Maggie Phillips, this is the culmination of 75 years of combined clinical experience, as well as 5 years of collaboration and feedback from countless seminars and therapists. Now these tried and true techniques are available to everyone.  Granted, we are getting to this story a bit late, as this book has been on the shelves for several months now. But the reception that we have received from what friends who have given the book and audio series out have said, to emails from caring fans, has been exceptionally positive. THey have all reported that symptomology has reduced greatly, and that friends, clients, and themselves are finding long-lasting, significant relief, which makes us exceptionally happy here.', 'Freedom From Pain - ', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'freedom-from-pain', '', '', '2013-02-12 23:38:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/?p=215', 1, 'post', '', 0),
(217, 1, '2013-03-06 18:38:25', '2013-03-06 18:38:25', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="InnerVision Homepage" href="http://www.kpfk.org/programs/118-innervisiontuesdays.html" target="_blank"><img style="vertical-align: middle;" alt="KPFK Logo" src="http://www.kpfk.org/templates/ja_purity/images/logo.png" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">On this episode (which also features <a title="Dr. Bonnie Goldstein''s homepage " href="http://www.drbonniegoldstein.com/" target="_blank">Bonnie Goldstein, PhD</a> of Lifespan Learning and <a title="Irving Yalom information " href="http://www.yalom.com/" target="_blank">Irving Yalom, M.D.</a>) of Inner Vision, Dr. Levine discussed his participation in this <a href="http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/01/29/ucla-presents-how-people-change-relationships-and-neuroplasticity-in-psychotherapy/">weekend''s attachment conference at UCLA</a>, as well as the origins of his interest in trauma.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">You can <a title="MP3 Download" href="http://archive.kpfk.org/mp3/kpfk_130305_130030ivtue.MP3" target="_blank">download</a> or <a title="Streaming Playlist version" href="http://archive.kpfk.org/m3u.php?mp3fil=13852" target="_blank">stream (M3u File)</a> the interview here (links will be deactivated by Early June)</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">(<a title="Future proofing the mp3 download link" href="images/stories/audio/KPFK_Inner_Vision_Tuesdays%20w_Nita.mp3" target="_blank">Download Permalink</a>)</p>', 'Peter Levine on Inner Vision with Dr. Nita Vallens', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'peter-levine-on-inner-vision-with-dr-nita-vallens', '', '', '2014-01-25 05:16:10', '2014-01-25 05:16:10', '', 0, 'http://somaticexperiencing.com/export/2013/03/06/peter-levine-on-inner-vision-with-dr-nita-vallens/', 3, 'post', '', 0),
